abstract: There is an unverified rumor that GEORGE I., King of the Hellenes, contemplates abdicating the throne of Greece. abstract: IN THE small hours of the morning a man, carrying a heavy suitcase, hurried down the deserted streets of the sleeping city. abstract: LARCHMONT, N.Y., Sept. 12. -- Mrs. Ina I. Nelson, wife of ex-Judge G. Marius Nelson, a wealthy resident of Larchmont, and her 6-year-old son, George Steward Nelson, were accidentally asphyxiated by gas in their home in Larchmont early today. abstract: BOSTON, Sept. 12. -- The August output of the Lake Superior mines was 20,487,300 pounds of fine copper. This compares with 20,964,200 in July and 19,276,625 in August, 1908. For the eight months of the year the figures are 157,360,600, or 6,480,766 pounds in excess of that for the same period last year. This is the largest eight months' production in the history of the Lake.

abstract: ROCHESTER, Minn., Sept 16. -- Gov. Johnson, who was operated on yesterday, spent a fairly easy day, considering the seriousness of his condition. abstract: THE first comprehensive translation of the tales* of Gustavo Becquer is worthy of note. Becquer's brief and sad life came to an end in 1870 -- he was born in 1836 -- and since then his fame has been steadily growing in his native land. abstract: WATERBURY, Conn., Sept. 18. -- Branislowas Kulwinski, 26 years old, was found dying in the woods near Union City this morning. abstract: PARIS, Sept. 18. -- Fresh enilvenment, which was much needed in the present languid life of the boulevards, was furnished on Thursday by the advent of a very pretty chauffeuse in charge of a taxicab. abstract: ST. PAUL, Minn., Sept. 21. -- One of the most remarkable tributes ever paid to the memory of a public man in Minnesota was accorded the late Gov. Johnson today. All banks, stores, and offices were closed, and buildings were draped in black and purple crape.

abstract: LEWES, Del., Sept. 22. -- Delaware got ahead of New York to-day in honoring the memory of Henry Hudson. abstract: PITTSBURG, Sept. 26. -- Bessemer iron and Connellsville coke divided interest in this market during the week just ended. The former leaped from $17.50, valleys, the price at which it had been first on Monday, to $18 on Friday, which is the minimum now for immediate delivery. For next year buyers are offering $18.50, while the furnace interests are asking $18.75 and $19, and are freely predicting $20 Bessemer before the end of November.

abstract: WASHINGTON, Sept. 29. -- A party of forty Chinese students will soon arrive in this country to study at American universities in preparation for civil service positions at home. abstract: The American courts have barred from citizenship Chinese, Japanese, Burmese, and their half-breeds. Will they bar Turks?
